            <entry xml:id="entry_7fsadyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ᵆfsadyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>ᵆfsæst</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æfsadun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>æfsast</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>насыщать</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>satiate</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>bafsad æj ærmæst</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ты только насыть его</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>just satiate him</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>92</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Метатеза из %i*sfad-%i ← %i*spād-%i. Восходит к <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*spāy- : *spāta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>насыщаться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>становиться упитанным</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в
                            каузативе</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in causative
                            form</note>
                        <gloss><q>насыщать</q></gloss></mentioned>. Прош. причастие %ispāta-%i было
                    взято в осетинском за основу наст. времени; стало быть, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*spāy-</w></mentioned> относится формально к ос. %iᵆfsadyn%i, как,
                    скажем, в <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>traho</w></mentioned> к <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>tracto</w></mentioned>; ср. в этом отношении <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ūdyn"/>. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>spai- : spata-</w>
                        <gloss><q>насыщаться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>sphāy-: sphāta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>жиреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>полнеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в каузативе</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">in causative form</note>
                        <gloss><q>откармливать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>насыщать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">спѣти</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>spetʼ</w></mentioned>. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsædyn"/>
                    ‘насыщаться’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsīs"/> ‘насыщение’.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр.
                            325</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p. 325</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"
                            /><biblScope>XII 266</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Metathesis from %i*sfad-%i ← %i*spād-%i. It traces back to
                        <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*spāy- : *spāta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>become full</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>become well-fed</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в
                            каузативе</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in causative
                            form</note>
                        <gloss><q>satiate</q></gloss></mentioned>. A past participle %ispāta-%i was
                    taken in Ossetic for the present tense stem; thus, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*spāy-</w></mentioned> is formally related to Ossetic %iᵆfsadyn%i, as,
                    for example, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>traho</w></mentioned> is related to <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>tracto</w></mentioned>; cf. in this relation <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ūdyn"/>. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>spai- : spata-</w>
                        <gloss><q>become full</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>sphāy-: sphāta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>fatten</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>put on weight</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в каузативе</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">in causative form</note>
                        <gloss><q>feed</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>satiate</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>spěti</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>спеть</w>
                        <gloss><q>ripen</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7fsædyn"/> ‘become full’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7fsīs"/> ‘satiation’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр.
                            325</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p. 325</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"
                            /><biblScope>XII 266</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
